# Foreach pattern in C macro



You can define a foreach macro like this. Useful when iterating over custom structures. 
```c

#define FOREACH(var)\
  for (var = 0; var < PREDEFINED_LEN; var++)

#define FOREACH(var, len)\
  for (var = 0; var < len; var++)

#define FOREACH_TYPE_T(ptr)\
  for (ptr = begin(); ptr != end(); ptr = get_next_ptr(ptr))
```

