#llvm #ir

Instrumenting functions' prologue and epilogue is not as straight forward as it seem.

To instrument every function's prologue: 
```c
   auto FirstI = &*F.getEntryBlock().begin();
   IRBuilder<> ProIRB(FirstI);
   CallInst *Prologue = ProIRB.CreateCall(CapacPrologue);

   DILocation *Loc =
       DILocation::get(F.getParent()->getContext(), 0, 0,
       F.getSubprogram());
  Prologue->setDebugLoc(Loc);
```
Note that The debug location is needed because of this error:
> inlinable function call in a function with debug info must have a !dbg location

The epilogue must cover all exit points of the function. This can be done by scanning for return instructions in the basic blocks. 
```c

   // Collect possible exit points
   std::vector<BasicBlock *> ReturningBlocks;
   for (BasicBlock &I : F)
     if (isa<ReturnInst>(I.getTerminator()))
       ReturningBlocks.push_back(&I);

   // Insert epilogue to all blocks
