#linux #os

Linux's kernel image is direct-mapped to the virtual address space. Physical addresses within the kernel can be translated into virtual addresses by simply adding a `PAGE_OFFSET`

```c
// in asm/page.h
#define __va(x)			((void *)((unsigned long)(x)+PAGE_OFFSET))

// in asm/io.h
static inline void *phys_to_virt(phys_addr_t address)
{
	return __va(address);
}
```

# References
- [understand006](https://www.kernel.org/doc/gorman/html/understand/understand006.html)

