#data-only-attack #attack

# Expressiveness
It is shown that data-only attack can achieve turing-complete execution under a certain condition [@hu2016dataoriented]. More specifically, there must be loop that is vulnerable to buffer overflow, that contain a corruptible switch condition. The original refer to this type of loop as a *gadget dispatcher*. 
This is an example:
```c
while (...){
  overflow(); // buffer overflow
  if (*type == NONE) break;
  if (*type == STREAM)
    *size = *(srv->cur_max); // dereference
  else {
    srv->typ = *type;    // assignment
    srv->total += *size; // addition
  }
  ///...
}
```
When the attacker can infinitely control the loop, he is able to set up the operands and run different instructions in a turing-complete manner.

